  "texts": [
    "Since x and y must have the same length, R n does not satisfy up-R, R-down, or R-refinability +.",
    "However, R n does satisfy R-com and R⇒win.",
    "For R⇒win, if xR n y and y ′ = ⟨y 1,..., y l ⟩ is an extension y = ⟨y 1,..., y k ⟩, let x ′ be the result of concatenating ⟨y k+1,..., y l ⟩ on to the end of x.",
    "Then clearly for every extension x ′′ of x, there is an extension y ′′ of y such that x ′′ R n y ′′, since we can use the same move of copying and concatenating.",
    "Thus, the structure F = ⟨2 <ω, ⊑, {R n } n∈N, RO(2 <ω, ⊑)⟩ is a full possibility frame."
  ],
